gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 124, Timberwolves 120
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Malik Monk’s season-high 39 points (5-8 3PT FG), the Kings defeated the Timberwolves, 124-120, in overtime. Domantas Sabonis added 21 points, 15 rebounds and eight assists for the Kings in the victory, while Jaden McDaniels tallied a career-high 26 points (5-7 3PT FG), along with seven rebounds for the Timberwolves in the losing effort. The Kings improve to 34-25 on the season, while the Timberwolves fall to 42-18.
